			<h1 class="m-bottom-1">A simple test of WordPress performance</h1>
			<p class="lead">Caching page output via Varnish or NGINX will bring the load time of nearly any cacheable page down well under a second. It is an easy win.</p>
			<p class="lead">The true test for your host is when you access your dashboard or a customer adds a product to their cart for checkout. Does that process feel sluggish and slow? The <strong class="txt-color-dark">backend performance</strong> of your WordPress site is how you can gauge how well your setup is performing.</p> 
			<p class="lead pad1 blue-alpha60">Our stack delivers consistently fast performance for all usage scenario's. That is why <a href="/ambassadors/" class="txt-color-mid">key members of the WordPress business community</a> choose Pagely. They know their business depends on their site performing well in all cases.</p>
